headlines.description: Alex Hornibrook threw four touchdown passes, three of them to Danny Davis, and No. 6 Wisconsin capped off the winningest season in school history by topping No. 11 Miami 34-24 in the Orange Bowl on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornibrook's 4 TDs carry Badgers over Miami, 34-24 in Orange

video.headline: Hornibrook's four scores lead Wisconsin past Miami

events.name: Washington Huskies at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: Trace McSorley threw for 342 yards and two touchdowns, Saquon Barkley ran for two more scores and No. 9 Penn State outlasted No. 12 Washington 35-28 in the Fiesta Bowl on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 9 Penn State tops No. 12 Washington 35-28 in Fiesta Bowl

video.headline: Penn State tops Washington in a thriller

events.name: Iowa State Cyclones at Memphis Tigers

headlines.description: Allen Lazard tied a Liberty Bowl record with 10 catches and put Iowa State ahead with a remarkable 5-yard touchdown reception in the third quarter Saturday, and the Cyclones beat No. 19 Memphis 21-20 on the Tigers' home field.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa State edges No. 19 Memphis 21-20 in Liberty Bowl

video.headline: Iowa State dispatches Memphis in Liberty Bowl

events.name: Louisville Cardinals at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson carries Miss State to 31-27 victory in TaxSlayer

video.headline: Mississippi State slows down Jackson, Louisville to win TaxSlayer Bowl
